node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 19, 2021. May be an image of phone, screen and text that says 'iPhone SE3 A14 Bionic Chip + 5G expected in early 2022 @theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
According to DigiTimes, Apple will launch an updated 4.7-inch iPhone SE in early 2022 with an A14 Bionic Chip and 5G support.

#Apple #iPhoneSE #tech #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 19, 2021. May be an image of phone, screen and text.

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, the upcoming iPhone models could feature an always-on display similar to that of the Apple Watch. The new iPhones will feature an LTPO OLED display, which would allow the display to be powered efficiently at a low brightness level and refresh rate. 

#Apple #iPhone12s #iPhone13 #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on July 18, 2021 tagging @rendersbyian. May be an image of laptop, screen and text that says 'MacBook Pro launching between September and November RENDERSBY IAN @theapplehub'.

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, Apple will launch redesigned 14” and 16” MacBook Pro models between September and November. The new models will go into production in the third quarter. Render from @rendersbyian 

#Apple #Mac #MacBookPro #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 15, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'New Emoji coming soon H M wIH @theapplehub Image from Emojipedia'.

node.text:
These are the candidates for Unicode Consortium’s Emoji 14.0 that could come to iPhone within the next year including a biting lip, low battery, person with a crown, heart hands, coral, saluting face, and more. These emoji are still in draft status and will need to be approved.

#Apple #Emoji #iPhone12 #iPhone13 #iPhone12s #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 14, 2021. May be an image of screen, television, laptop and text that says '30-32" Mac to feature M1X or M2X chip @theapplehub'.

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, Apple is working on a larger iMac with a more powerful M1X or M2X chip. Apple could launch the new model by the end of the year.

#Apple #Mac #iMac #iMacPro #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 13, 2021. May be an image of phone and text that says 'MagSafe Battery Pack now available for $99 @theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
Apple has launched a new MagSafe Battery Pack for $99 and is compatible with the iPhone 12, iPhone 12 mini, iPhone 12 Pro, and iPhone 12 Pro Max. While plugged in, it can charge an iPhone up to 15W.

#Apple #iPhone12 #iPhone12Pro #MagSafe #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on July 07, 2021 tagging @ar72014. May be an image of text that says '2022 iPhones new front design 一 @theapplehub Wallpaperfrom @ar72014'.

node.text:
Apple is expected to replace the notch next year in favor of a hole punch cutout for the camera and sensors. Do you like this change?

#Apple #iPhone13 #iPhone14 #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 07, 2021. May be an image of phone and text that says 'iPhone 12 S larger camera module @theapplehub From "UnclePanPan" on Weibo'.

node.text:
A new image shared on Weibo shows an iPhone 12 Pro in a case for the upcoming iPhone 12🅂 Pro. The new camera module will be huge!

#Apple #iPhone12s #iPhone13 #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on July 04, 2021 tagging @everythingapplepro. May be an image of text that says 'iPhone 12 S reverse wireless charging @theapplehub Fromeverythingapplepro'.

node.text:
According to Max Weinbach via @everythingapplepro, Apple will include a larger wireless charging coil on the upcoming iPhone models, which could be used to enable reverse wireless charging. Reverse wireless charging would enable users to charge their AirPods or Apple Watch on an iPhone.

#Apple #iPhone12S #iPhone13 #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on July 02, 2021. May be an image of phone, laptop, screen and text that says '2022 iPad to feature next- gen 3nm chip @theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
According to Nikkei Asia, Apple will launch their next-gen 3nm chip tech on an iPad next year, likely the 2022 iPad Pro models. Apple’s 2022 iPhone models will feature a 4nm A16 chip.

#Apple #iPad #iPadPro #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on July 02, 2021 tagging @rendersbyian. May be an image of laptop, screen and text.

node.text:
According to DigiTimes, Apple will launch the long-awaited 14” and 16” MacBook Pro models with Mini-LED displays and Apple silicon processors in September. Render from @rendersbyian

#Apple￼ #MacBook #MacBookPro #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on June 30, 2021. May be an image of phone, screen and text that says 'iPad Air with OLED display coming next year @theapplehub theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
According to The Elec, Apple will launch a 5th gen iPad Air with an OLED display next year, followed by another OLED iPad in 2023.

#Apple #iPad #iPadAir #AppleHub
